# PRMS Codebase Guide For Cursor

## 1. Purpose

This file is the short-entry context for any AI agent working in this repo.
Read this file first, then open only the backend/frontend files directly related to the task.

Primary goal:

- avoid loading the whole repo every time
- keep changes aligned between backend and frontend
- preserve the existing contracts, patterns, and naming already used in PRMS

## 2. Repo Map

This is a fullstack repo with backend at root and frontend in `prms-web`.

### Backend

- stack: Java 17, Spring Boot 3.5.x, Spring Security, JPA, PostgreSQL, JWT, OpenAPI
- root package: `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms`
- resources: `src/main/resources`
- server port: `8080`
- main class: `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms/PrmsApplication.java`
- config entry: `src/main/resources/application.yml`

### Frontend

- stack: Angular 20 standalone, NG-ZORRO, ngx-translate, ngx-spinner
- app root: `prms-web/src/app`
- static assets: `prms-web/public/assets`
- frontend dev port: `4200`
- FE API base URL config: `prms-web/public/assets/config/app-config.json`

## 3. Core Architecture

### Backend flow

Standard flow is:

- `controller -> service -> repository -> entity`

Important files:

- controllers: `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms/controller`
- services: `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms/service`
- service implementations: `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms/service/impl`
- repositories: `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms/repository`
- entities: `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms/entity`
- DTOs: `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms/dto`

Do not bypass this layering unless the task explicitly requires a refactor.

### Frontend flow

Standard flow is:

- `page/component -> feature service -> core BaseService -> backend API`

Important files:

- app routes: `prms-web/src/app/app.routes.ts`
- app bootstrap/providers: `prms-web/src/app/app.config.ts`
- HTTP wrapper: `prms-web/src/app/core/services/base-service.ts`
- auth interceptor: `prms-web/src/app/core/guards/app-interceptor.ts`
- storage/token handling: `prms-web/src/app/core/services/storage-service.ts`
- layout/navigation: `prms-web/src/app/shared/layout/main-layout/main-layout.ts`
- menu map: `prms-web/src/app/shared/utils/navigation.model.ts`

## 4. Shared Contracts Between BE And FE

### Unified response

Backend uses `BaseResponse`:

- file: `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms/dto/BaseResponse.java`
- fields: `timestamp`, `body`, `message`, `status`, `code`

Frontend expects the same wrapper via:

- `prms-web/src/app/shared/utils/api-response.ts`

Any backend response shape change must be updated on frontend in the same task.

### Search/paging contract

Backend search request base:

- `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms/dto/SearchRequest.java`

Current common pattern:

- paged endpoint: `POST /api/v1/<entity>/page`
- request body extends `SearchRequest`
- fields commonly used: `keyword`, `voided`, `pageIndex`, `pageSize`, `ids`

Frontend services and list pages follow the same contract.

### Validation/error contract

Backend validation helper:

- `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms/service/BaseService.java`

Current behavior:

- service validates request with `validation(...)`
- 400 responses may return `body` as field-message map
- frontend pages often read `raw.body` and show combined validation messages

Backend exception mapping:

- `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms/exception/GlobalExceptionHandler.java`

Do not change error body format lightly.

## 5. Authentication And Request Lifecycle

### Backend auth

Main files:

- controller: `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms/controller/AuthenticationController.java`
- security config: `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms/config/SecurityConfig.java`
- JWT filter: `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms/config/JwtAuthenticationFilter.java`
- JWT service: `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms/service/JwtService.java`
- auth service impl: `src/main/java/com/tranhuudat/prms/service/impl/AuthenticationServiceImpl.java`

Notes:

- public endpoints are controlled by `SecurityConfig.PUBLIC_ENDPOINTS`
- most APIs require authentication
- CORS currently allows `http://localhost:4200`
- logout endpoint is `/api/v1/auth/logout`

### Frontend auth

Main files:

- auth service: `prms-web/src/app/pages/auth/auth-service.ts`
- interceptor: `prms-web/src/app/core/guards/app-interceptor.ts`
- route guards: `prms-web/src/app/core/guards/auth-guard.ts`, `prms-web/src/app/core/guards/login-guard.ts`
- token storage: `prms-web/src/app/core/services/storage-service.ts`
- current user store: `prms-web/src/app/core/services/store-service.ts`

Request flow:

1. Interceptor adds `Authorization` header if access token exists.
2. Interceptor also adds `Accept-language`.
3. On `401`, frontend tries refresh token endpoint.
4. If refresh fails, user is signed out and redirected to `/login`.

## 6. Main Business Domains

### Authentication

Backend:

- `AuthenticationController`
- `AuthenticationServiceImpl`
- entities: `User`, `Token`, `RefreshToken`

Frontend:

- `pages/auth/login`
- `pages/auth/auth-service.ts`

### Users

Backend:

- controller: `UserController`
- service: `UserService`, `UserServiceImpl`
- repository: `UserRepository`
- DTOs: `dto/user/*`

Frontend:

- routes: `prms-web/src/app/pages/management/users/user.routes.ts`
- page: `prms-web/src/app/pages/management/users/user-list/*`
- service: `prms-web/src/app/pages/management/users/services/user.service.ts`
- role service: `prms-web/src/app/pages/management/users/services/role.service.ts`

Related endpoints:

- `/api/v1/users/current`
- `/api/v1/users/{id}`
- `/api/v1/users/page`
- `/api/v1/users`
- `/api/v1/users/{id}/password`

### Projects

Backend:

- controller: `ProjectController`
- service: `ProjectService`, `ProjectServiceImpl`
- repository: `ProjectRepository`
- DTOs: `dto/project/*`
- entity: `Project`

Frontend:

- route: `/project`
- page: `prms-web/src/app/pages/project/project-list/*`
- popup child component: `prms-web/src/app/pages/project/project-tasks/*`
- service: `prms-web/src/app/pages/project/services/project.service.ts`
- models: `prms-web/src/app/pages/project/models/*`

Notes:

